Two reformed robbery convicts infamous for crime in the 1960s to the mid-80s say they had a ruthlessly enforced code that barred gang members from using brutal force against women, the elderly and children. 

John Kiriamiti, who wrote My Life in Crime, alongside his fellow gang member George Githenji revealed that whenever any of the members broke that rule, he would be shot dead. 



