In the world of crime, Kiriamiti was known as Jack Zollo, whereas Githenji was GG, and together, they confess, they stole millions of shillings. 

“It was simply unacceptable to, especially defile, rape or use unnecessary brutal force against our victims. It was not like today’s gangs that shoot people indiscriminately, sexually assault and use all other forms of brutal force against victims,” Kiriamiti told the Nation. 






George Githenji, alias GG, a reformed gangster who worked with John Kiriamiti.
Photo credit: Joseph Kanyi | Nation Media Group

 

Reserved for police 



